{"type": "root", "attrs": {"icon": "/nodes/sop/MOPS--Explode-1.1/mops_misc_05.svg", "type": "node", "context": "sop", "internal": "Explode", "version": "1.1", "namespace": "MOPS"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["MOPs Explode"], "extent": [0, 17]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Splits polygon primitives into individual MOPs packed primitives."], "extent": [51, 124]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["MOPs Explode breaks a polygon mesh apart into MOPs primitives, so that each primitive/face can be moved individually. \nYou can optionally use a primitive attribute or K-means clustering to create grouped ", {"type": "q", "text": ["chunks"]}, " instead of breaking apart every face."], "extent": [124, 376]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator works in three steps: first, an orientation frame is computed on the source object. Next, the object is split into MOPs primitives\nbased on either the primitive numbers, a primitive attribute, or K-means clustering (via the Cluster SOP). Finally, the orientation from\nthe original mesh points is transferred onto the MOPs primitives as the p@mops_orient attribute, which makes the generated pieces\nfollow the orientation of the source mesh as much as possible."], "extent": [376, 852]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Overview"], "extent": [852, 867], "body": []}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [867, 876], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 0, "text": ["Geometry"], "extent": [876, 887], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Plug in geometry that should be converted to instances in here."], "extent": [887, 956]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [956, 968], "body": [{"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["General"], "extent": [968, 983], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Compute Source Orient"], "extent": [983, 1007], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Compute the orientation frame of the input mesh. If your mesh doesn\u2019t already have a p@orient attribute, this should be enabled."], "extent": [1031, 1169]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "compute_orient"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Compute Source Orient"], "extent": [1169, 1197], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Compute N/Up"], "extent": [1197, 1216], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Compute normal and up vectors on the input mesh, to be used in creating the orientation frame."], "extent": [1238, 1342]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "compute_N_up"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Style"], "extent": [1342, 1349], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which the initial N and up vectors are computed. See the Polyframe SOP for details."], "extent": [1364, 1471]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "style"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Attribute Name"], "extent": [1471, 1487], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If Style is set to ", {"type": "q", "text": ["Texture UV"]}, ", the vector point attribute to read to determine the directionality of the tangent and bitangent vectors."], "extent": [1507, 1654]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "attribname"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Custom Up Vector"], "extent": [1654, 1672], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["If enabled, use this up vector instead of the one computed via the above parameters."], "extent": [1698, 1792]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "custom_up_vector"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Invert Normal"], "extent": [1792, 1807], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Invert the computed normal."], "extent": [1825, 1862]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "invert_N"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Invert Up"], "extent": [1862, 1873], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Invert the computed up vector."], "extent": [1892, 1932]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "invert_up"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Define Pieces"], "extent": [1932, 1953], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Method"], "extent": [1953, 1962], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The method by which pieces are split up."], "extent": [1984, 2029], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Primitive Number: each primitive becomes its own MOPs packed primitive."], "extent": [2029, 2111]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Piece Attribute: The primitive attribute to use to differentiate pieces. Each unique attribute value gets its own MOPs primitive."], "extent": [2111, 2251]}, {"blevel": 10, "type": "bullet", "indent": 8, "text": ["Clustering: Use K-means clustering to naturally group primitives into chunks. See the Cluster SOP for details."], "extent": [2251, 2372]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "piece_method"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Piece Attribute"], "extent": [2372, 2389], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The attribute to use for determining pieces if the Method is set to Piece Attribute. This can be an integer or string attribute."], "extent": [2414, 2552]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "piece_attribute"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Id Offset"], "extent": [2552, 2563], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The starting value for generated piece i@id attributes."], "extent": [2582, 2647]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "id_offset"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Name Prefix"], "extent": [2647, 2660], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The prefix to use as the basis for the s@name attribute of each piece. This can be used to ensure packed primitives from multiple\n    streams all have unique names."], "extent": [2681, 2855]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "name_prefix"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visualize Pieces"], "extent": [2855, 2873], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Apply a color attribute to the pieces before packing in order to better differentiate the generated pieces."], "extent": [2896, 3013]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "do_viz_pieces"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visualization Seed"], "extent": [3013, 3033], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The seed to use for generating random colors."], "extent": [3051, 3106]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "viz_seed"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Transfer Orient"], "extent": [3106, 3128], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["See the Attribute Transfer SOP for details."], "extent": [3128, 3172]}]}], "text": "Parameters"}], "title": ["MOPs Explode"], "summary": ["Splits polygon primitives into individual MOPs packed primitives."]}